From: home-ops downstream
Subject: Always extract audio via external ffmpeg

faster-whisper's internal PyAV-based decoder fails on certain DTS
streams with `Frame does not match AudioFifo parameters`, leaving
PyAV in a corrupted state that segfaults the entire process on the
next decode call. Documented upstream:

  https://github.com/Purfview/whisper-standalone-win/issues/236

subgen already has `extract_audio_track_to_memory()` which uses
ffmpeg-python (subprocess) and correctly handles the same files
that crash PyAV. The original code only invoked this path when a
file had multiple audio tracks; this patch makes external ffmpeg
extraction the default for any file with at least one audio track,
so faster-whisper always receives clean mono 16kHz WAV bytes.

